Name: Scietetics Ful V Tech Element Transfer System
Short description: [caption id="attachment_63527" align="alignnone" width="163"] FUL V TECH[/caption]
Description:
Scietetics Ful V Tech Element Transfer System 
is a concentrated blend of the best fulvic acids (five types "V") catered for plant system fortification as well as commercial Gardening irrigation strategy. This clean formula will stabilize basic fertilizer solutions and increase solubility through emitters and injectors. Expect higher qualitative characteristics out of the crop and more response from fertilizers used in compatibility. NPK is 0-0-0 and the product is registered as a molybdenum fertilizer.
Directions for use:

Mix 5-10 ml per gallon of water.
Use with every watering as needed.
Mix well and adjust pH accordingly. Shake well before use.
Foliar Applications. 5 ml per gallon of water.
Use only as directed and keep out of reach of children.

Name: Scietetics MagCal
Short description: Key Information Scientific Foundation: As a product from Scietetics, a company focused on science-based plant nutrition, MagCal is formulated using cu
Description:
Key Information
Scientific Foundation: As a product from Scietetics, a company focused on science-based plant nutrition, MagCal is formulated using cutting-edge agricultural research and technology.
Supplemental Nature: Rather than replacing your existing nutrient program, MagCal is intended to complement and enhance it, potentially addressing specific nutritional gaps
Versatility: MagCal can be used in a variety of cultivation methods, including traditional soil-based agriculture and hydroponics.


DIRECTIONS FOR USE
Shake well before each use.
Mix 1-2 mL/gallon of nutrient solution
Use with every watering as needed
Mix well and adjust pH accordingly
Use only as directed, keep out of children keep out of reach of children

MagCal
Scietetics MagCal is a supplemental primary and micro-nutrient source to be used in conjunction with your standard feeding program. The industry standard low nitrogen formulation is densely packed giving you more concentration at lower dosage rates. Perfect for any situation where supplemental Ca & Mg is desired.

MORE INFORMATION

MagCal is likely designed for flexible use across different growth stages. It can be particularly beneficial during periods of rapid growth or when plants show signs of calcium or magnesium deficiency. For precise dosage and application instructions, growers should refer to the product label or consult with Scietetics directly, as rates may vary depending on the specific crop and growing conditions

Name: Accurate pH
Short description: Accurate pH 4 This meter utilizes the same body and electronics as the CWP Instruments Accurate pH 3 but has the added advantage of a larger corded el
Description:
Accurate pH 4

This meter utilizes the same body and electronics as the CWP Instruments Accurate pH 3 but has the added advantage of a larger corded electrode. The larger electrode enhances the meters electronic circuitry making it not only very accurate but also it has very stable readings.

  • The corded electrode allows the user to test a large body of solution without the chance of dropping the meter’s body into the solution being tested.
  • The electrode is replaceable and the meter has a 2 point calibration system for superior accuracy.
  • Both calibration screws are located inside the battery compartment.

    The meter has low power consumption circuitry with an auto OFF feature. It uses four 1.5 volt button type batteries.

Name: DLI-DIODE-Series-LED Toplighting LED Fixture
Short description: DLI Toplighting fixtures are designed to deliver high levels of photosynthetic photon flux (PPF) values with optimal angled vertical light uniformity.
Description:
DLI Toplighting fixtures are designed to deliver high levels of photosynthetic photon flux (PPF) values with optimal angled vertical light uniformity. The unique design of the lens creates a high uniform light distribution over the canopy.

The fixtures are constructed in a slim water-proof design and suspended above the plant canopy with the easy-hang system.
Toplighting fixture (long) Features
Extra Low-Profile Housing (Ideal for low ceilings)
Venturi effect (For optimal cooling)
High Output (Up to 1000 µmol/s)
IP65 Waterproof (Protected against water jets from any direction)
Time for Improvement
For Decades growers have settled for lighting options that are not 100% tailored for their use and crop. Grow light manufacturers are always trying to appease the mass populations of growers, rather than honing in on exactly what they need for optimal performance, yields, and most important quality.

The engineering principles behind the DLI Toplighting Fixtures are a culmination of over a decade of research and development. The team works with a ranging group of some of the best horticulturists around the globe; each who specialise in plant and varietal specific production processes for the ornamental, and commercial flower market. Dutch Lighting Innovations has allowed these groups a new level of consistency, reliability, and quality unparalleled in the niche world of growing the best flowers and plants on Earth!

For a uniform plant a uniform pattern is required
A percentage of harvestable plant height can suffer from lack of light due to dense canopy foliage; which will result in fewer flowers. Because of the unique light distribution the Toplighting system will provide High PAR PPF at an optimized coverage angle making sure the whole plant is activated by light.

Extensive trials have shown bigger leaves and flowers at the lower portions on the plant. The Toplighting fixtures emit very little heat and require no active cooling minimizing leaf burn.

Weight & Dimensions:
DIMENSIONS:
990 x 232 x 85 mm
39 x 9.1 x 3.4 INCH

WEIGHT:
8 kg / 17.6 lbs

Power
INPUT VOLTAGE: 220 ~ 400V
INPUT VOLTAGE RANGE: ± 10%
RATED POWER: See product label

Name: Athena Bloom B
Short description: Athena Bloom B is a simple and clean 2-part formula designed for the flowering stage of growth for fruit and flower-producing plants. We blend top of
Description:
Athena Bloom B is a simple and clean 2-part formula designed for the flowering stage of growth for fruit and flower-producing plants. We blend top of the line macronutrients and chelated micronutrients to achieve greater nutrient uptake ability across a wider pH range in any combination of grow method, water-type and media. This 2-part blended liquid formula should be used in equal amounts during the flowering phase to stimulate the rapid onset of bud production, increase flowering sites, and promote high-quality yields. Formulas are sediment free and are compatible with all dosing and irrigation systems in including fine dripper heads. Small amounts of micro-particles are occasionally visible in some conditions but will not affect mineral balance or system compatibility. Application Rates Add 2-7 mL of Athena Bloom B per gallon of water during the flowering phase. See Feed Schedules for specific application recommendations. Best Practices
  • Shake well before use.
  • Use clean measuring instruments--do not put anything into the bottle.
  • Always use equal parts of Athena Bloom A & B to maintain proper mineral ratios.
  • Monitor EC regularly and adjust accordingly based on crop and growth stage.
  • Adjust pH to proper levels after mixing all fertilizers and additives.
  • Do not combine in undiluted form.
  • Store closed in original packaging at a temperature between 45° F and 85° F.

Name: Athena Stack
Short description: Stack is a natural plant nutrient made from kelp extract. The nutrients in Stack encourage healthy growth and flowering. Stack gives the plant tools t
Description: Stack is a natural plant nutrient made from kelp extract. The nutrients in Stack encourage healthy growth and flowering. Stack gives the plant tools to reach its full genetic potential. When used as a foliar or root drench, Stack helps correct minor potassium deficiencies. Instructions for use: May be used as a foliar spray or root drench, one application weekly. Safe for use in irrigation systems. Stack contains organic ingredients and may separate in storage. Shake well before use. Application Timing: Apply Stack from the final week of vegetative growth to week 4-5 of flowering, or once plants stop growing vertically. Root Drench: Mix 1-2ml per gallon of water in a weekly mix. May be mixed with regular fertilizer recipe. Add last to reservoir. Foliar Spray: Mix 7ml per gallon water and spray thoroughly once weekly. Spray with lights off and allow to dry before turning on. Do not spray past week 3 flower. Transplant Use: Mix 2ml per gallon water and bare root soak for 30-60 seconds prior to transplanting or water in solution after transplanting. Stack may reduce transplant stress and improves plant vigor. Seed Treatment: Mix 4ml per gallon water and soak seed for 1-2 minutes before planting. Stack may increase germination rates and plant vigor.

Name: Athena Balance
Short description: Athena Balance is a simple formula of potassium silicate specifically concentrated to buffer irrigation water and stabilize to ideal pH. Silicon addit
Description:
Athena Balance is a simple formula of potassium silicate specifically concentrated to buffer irrigation water and stabilize to ideal pH. Silicon additionally benefits plant growth, stem structure, stress reduction, water usage (osmoregulation), and nutrient utilization.

Commercial growers find better results, particularly with reverse osmosis (RO) water, when buffering first with Athena Balance. Pure RO water has unstable chemical structure that can trap other nutrients when added without a buffer. Athena Balance adds just enough to the water to create a more homogenous fertilizer solution and reduce the need to pH adjust after mixing.

Formula is sediment-free and is compatible with mechanical dosing systems (Dosatron). Athena Balance is not recommended for electronic dosing systems (Netafim).

Name: Athena Cuts Rooting Gel Compound
Short description: In stock and ready to ship! Athena Cuts Rooting Gel is a premium rooting gel formulated to propagate new plants from stem and leaf cuttings of mother
Description:
In stock and ready to ship!
Athena Cuts Rooting Gel is a premium rooting gel formulated to propagate new plants from stem and leaf cuttings of mother plants. It is formulated with an essential plant hormone that promotes rapid root generation and growth.

This water-based gel coats and seals the tissue around the cut stem. The contains a blend of hormones, nutrients, and vitamins that are easily absorbed by the plant to promote abundant root cell development. 

Athena Cuts may be used on any type of cutting, including woody, herbaceous, flowers, ornamentals, vegetables, and fruit trees.

APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS

Squeeze a small amount of Athena Cuts Rooting Gel into a separate container.
Take cuttings from healthy mother plants and trim to 2-8 inch length.
Make cuts at a 45-degree angle on the stem.
Dip the cut end of the stem into Athena Cuts gel to the desired depth or immerse in water until ready to be dipped.
After Athena Cuts gel has been applied, place cuttings into a cloning system or rooting medium.
Depending on the variety, roots may appear within a few days or weeks of dipping. Transplant clones once the cuttings have rooted.

BEST PRACTICES

Take cuttings only from new growth on healthy mother plants.
Do not dip cuttings directly into container.
Discard used gel, do not reuse.

Name: Spray-N-Grow Micronutrients
Short description: Foliar feeding provides fast absorption of nutrients- results can be almost immediate. It’s 8-20 times more effective than root feeding. Foliar Feeding is not just a quick fix for deficiencies. Provide additional nutrients to increase yield and quality. Micronutrients, calcium and supplemental fertilizer are often applied to plants through foliar feeding. With most plants, foliar feeding augments- not replaces- a standard root feeding program.\n\nFoliar feeding is easy. Nutrients and a sprayer are all the equipment needed.
Description:
Spray-N-Grow Micronutrients 8 oz

Get More, Bigger, Tastier Fruits, Vegetables & Flowers
It's Like Vitamins for Your Plants™

Spray-N-Grow Micronutrients is a unique blend of 17 naturally occurring micronutrients that is proven to produce:

• more, larger, earlier blooms
• bigger, tastier fruits and vegetables
• stronger, healthier plants with larger roots

Spray-N-Grow's micronutrients are not found in fertilizer but are required for plants to reach their maximum potential. Fertilizer provides food for plants and micronutrients "are like vitamins for your plants™".

Proven by independent scientific research, Spray-N-Grow Micronutrients is 100% guaranteed to produce results on ALL plants - vegetables, fruits, flowers, shrubs, cactus, houseplants and EVEN trees.

Created by our founder Bill Muskopf, a chemist and avid gardener, Spray-N-Grow is made with natural ingredients, is nontoxic and safe for people, plants and pets. Spray-N-Grow Micronutrients is a foliar feed and easy to use. For more product information, see details below.

Spray-N-Grow Micronutrients is the key product in the complete nutrition Perfect Blend Kit.

Name: Silicium Bloom
Short description: SiLicium is beneficial for the regulation and the absorption of macro and micronutrients by the plant via xylem to the shoots and leaves. Silicon is translocated as anion, monosilicic acid, resulting as a silicon-cellulose membrane throughout the epidermal tissue. Found to have association with phosphorous and calcium ions, this process in which plant biomass enriches its level of silicon is called monosilicic acid polymerization.
Description:
Silicium Bloom 
SiLICIUM Bloom

During 12/12 flower cycles, switch to SiLICIUM Bloom in efforts to promote larger flowers and fruits as well as regulate “salt stress” caused from excess K/Na molecules. The ancillary effect of monosilicic acid and fulvic agents encourage the facilitation of phosphorous and calcium, but also simultaneously reduce toxicity of heavy metals, aluminum, and manganese within the plant system. Formulated specifically for budding and fruiting cycles, SiLICIUM Bloom ™ provides silicon in the conjunctional form serving as a biological chelate.

SiLICIUM mono-silicic acid also ensures that the plant stomata diameter is decreased, which helps regulates moisture loss thereby enhancing the mobility of various macro and micro nutritional elements throughout the crop.

Increased resistance and protection against diseases.
Protection against diseases, drought, heat and other environmental stressors during vegetative and budding development.
SiLICIUM mono-silicic acid also ensures that the plant stomata diameter is decreased.
Dosage

Use a minimum of 15mL per 100 Liters OR .5ML per 1 gal of feeding water throughout the growing cycle.

ALWAYS mix SiLICIUM with Tap or RO water before any other nutrients.

Name: SiLICIUM mono si
Description:
Key Information
SiLicium facilitates the absorption and regulation of macro and micronutrients within plants through xylem, enhancing their growth and development. It strengthens stems, leaves, and overall biomass, while also increasing resistance to diseases, drought, heat, and environmental stresses during vegetative and budding stages.
The application of SiLicium through the root system results in robust plant growth, with faster root development and stronger stems and leaves. This silicon-rich structure facilitates the transport of essential elements such as calcium and phosphorus, leading to tighter node stacking and increased flowering sites. Accelerated growth rates are achieved through enhanced cellular structures within the plant.
For optimal results, it is recommended to use a dosage of at least 15mL per 100 Liters or 0.5mL per 1 gallon of feeding water throughout the entire growing cycle. It is crucial to mix SiLicium with tap or RO water before adding any other nutrients to ensure proper integration and effectiveness.
DERIVED FROM
Boric Acid
Potassium Silicate
Sodium Molybdenum
Also Contains non-plant food ingredient
1.4% Silica (SiO2) from Potassium Silicate
SiLicium offers multifaceted benefits for plant growth and development

Facilitates the absorption and regulation of macro and micronutrients via xylem, enhancing overall plant health.
Strengthens stems, leaves, and biomass while increasing resistance to diseases, drought, heat, and environmental stresses during vegetative and budding stages.
Application through the root system results in robust growth, promoting faster root development and stronger plant structures.
Enhances transport of essential elements like calcium and phosphorus, leading to tighter node stacking and increased flowering sites.
Accelerates growth rates through improved cellular structures within the plant.
SiLicium
For optimal results, follow recommended dosage guidelines:

Use a minimum of 15mL per 100 Liters or 0.5mL per 1 gallon of feeding water throughout the growing cycle.
Always mix SiLicium with tap or RO water before adding any other nutrients to ensure proper integration and effectiveness.

The application of SiLICIUM through the root system results in increased resistance and protection against diseases, drought, heat and other environmental stressors during vegetative and budding development. Using SiLicium, your plants will root faster and develop stronger stems, leaves and plant biomass overall.

Key Information
SiLicium facilitates the absorption and regulation of macro and micronutrients within plants through xylem, enhancing their growth and development. It strengthens stems, leaves, and overall biomass, while also increasing resistance to diseases, drought, heat, and environmental stresses during vegetative and budding stages.
The application of SiLicium through the root system results in robust plant growth, with faster root development and stronger stems and leaves. This silicon-rich structure facilitates the transport of essential elements such as calcium and phosphorus, leading to tighter node stacking and increased flowering sites. Accelerated growth rates are achieved through enhanced cellular structures within the plant.
For optimal results, it is recommended to use a dosage of at least 15mL per 100 Liters or 0.5mL per 1 gallon of feeding water throughout the entire growing cycle. It is crucial to mix SiLicium with tap or RO water before adding any other nutrients to ensure proper integration and effectiveness.
DERIVED FROM
Boric Acid
Potassium Silicate
Sodium Molybdenum
Also Contains non-plant food ingredient
1.4% Silica (SiO2) from Potassium Silicate
SiLicium offers multifaceted benefits for plant growth and development

Facilitates the absorption and regulation of macro and micronutrients via xylem, enhancing overall plant health.
Strengthens stems, leaves, and biomass while increasing resistance to diseases, drought, heat, and environmental stresses during vegetative and budding stages.
Application through the root system results in robust growth, promoting faster root development and stronger plant structures.
Enhances transport of essential elements like calcium and phosphorus, leading to tighter node stacking and increased flowering sites.
Accelerates growth rates through improved cellular structures within the plant.

Use a minimum of 15mL per 100 Liters or 0.5mL per 1 gallon of feeding water throughout the growing cycle.
Always mix SiLicium with tap or RO water before adding any other nutrients to ensure proper integration and effectiveness.

Name: Multi
Short description: Key Information Patented oil-and-water emulsification technology clove, rosemary and thyme Formulated specifically for thrips but effective on almost
Description:
Key Information
Patented oil-and-water emulsification technology clove, rosemary and thyme

Formulated specifically for thrips but effective on almost ALL plant and pest and topical diseases
Downloads
DIRECTIONS FOR USE
Shake bottle very well before decanting any product for measurement
Mix RO or tap water at the proposed rates: 15mL/gal for maintenance 30mL/gal for infestation
Shake solution very well before spraying on plants to ensure thoroughly mixed.
For best results combine with 5mL/gal for Maintenance 10mL/gal infestation
Multi is a proprietary mixture utilizing commonly found food based ingredients recognized according to 25(b) exemption as safe and effective for integrated pest management practices. This recipe has be found exceptionally effective for thrips and Fungus gnats, but is not limited to eradicating and controlling mites, aphids, whitefly, and other soft-soft-boiled insects in their various life stages including eggs.
MORE INFORMATION
Multi is formulated using common food-based ingredients that are recognized as safe and effective under the FIFRA 25(b) exemption. This exemption allows for certain minimum-risk pesticides to be marketed without going through the formal EPA registration process, provided they meet specific criteria. Kills thrips, whiteflies, aphids, mites and eggs upon contact.Insecticide, Miticide, Fungicide, & Bactericide

Name: Agrowlyte Stop PM
Description:
Excellence in Agriculture & Healthy Food 
Proven Performance
Agrowlyte is field-tested and scientifically backed to clean, protect, and optimize systems—without harming plants, soil, or water quality. From irrigation pipes to propagation trays, our solution works where it matters most.
​
Effortless Integration
Whether you're running a 10-acre organic farm or a high-volume processing facility, Agrowlyte is built to fit seamlessly into your existing operations. No special equipment. No retraining. Just measurable results from day one.
 
Cost-Saving Efficiency
Save on labor, reduce equipment replacements, and eliminate the need for harsh chemical treatments. Agrowlyte’s optimized low-dose formulas ensure long-term efficiency at a fraction of the cost.

Safe & Sustainable

​
Certified & Compliant
From organic certifications to food-grade sanitation standards, Agrowlyte meets industry requirements and exceeds expectations. Our customers rely on us for peace of mind and regulatory confidence.
